## Accessibility Checklist

Based on observations from reference sites:

- [ ] All interactive elements have visible focus indicators
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG 2.1 AA (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- [ ] Error states use icon + text, not color alone
- [ ] Form labels are always visible (not placeholder-only)
- [ ] Touch targets are ≥44x44px for mobile
- [ ] Keyboard navigation follows logical tab order
- [ ] Motion can be disabled (prefers-reduced-motion support)
- [ ] Images have alt text (observed where visible)

